Definition.WordDefinition:
Vaginal \Vag"i*nal\, a. [Cf. F. vaginal.] [1913 Webster] 1. Of or pertaining to a vagina; resembling a vagina, or sheath; thecal; as, a vaginal synovial membrane; the vaginal process of the temporal bone. [1913 Webster]
2. (Anat.) Of or pertaining to the vagina of the genital canal; as, the vaginal artery. [1913 Webster]
vaginal adj : of or relating to the vagina; "vaginal suppository"
